title: Sunny weather and above average seasonal temperatures expected in Central Florida on Saturday - Orlando Sentinel
text:
Sunny weather and above average seasonal temperatures expected in Central Florida on Saturday Spectrum News 13 By Elainie Barraza | ebarraza@orlandosentinel.com | Orlando Sentinel PUBLISHED: December 20, 2025 at 9:12 AM EST Getting your Trinity Audio player ready... A chilly start to Saturday with temperatures forecast to rebound into the 70s is expected in Central Florida, Spectrum News 13 meteorologist Katie Garch said.
Plenty of sunshine is also expected throughout the day, Garch said. Temperatures are above average for this time of year but cooler than yesterday.
The high today will be 75 degrees and the low will be 53 degrees.
